00:00:02,069 --> 00:00:04,304
(grunting)

2
00:00:04,304 --> 00:00:10,077
♪

3
00:00:10,077 --> 00:00:11,345
Hmm.

4
00:00:11,345 --> 00:00:14,448
(grunting)

5
00:00:14,448 --> 00:00:16,149
Pitiful, Nehalem.

6
00:00:16,149 --> 00:00:17,551
You can't stop the attacks

7
00:00:17,551 --> 00:00:20,587
of my Juggernaut Maximum
forever, you know.

8
00:00:20,587 --> 00:00:24,057
Huh, you really think so?

9
00:00:24,057 --> 00:00:28,295
♪

10
00:00:28,295 --> 00:00:29,897
I got you!

11
00:00:29,897 --> 00:00:31,298
You've got nothing.

12
00:00:31,298 --> 00:00:33,433
You never stood a
chance against me.

13
00:00:33,433 --> 00:00:34,601
Say what?

14
00:00:34,601 --> 00:00:37,938
I'm gonna ride up to the
next grade right now.

15
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:41,642
(gasping)

16
00:00:41,642 --> 00:00:44,278
Now ride the Vanguard!

17
00:00:46,079 --> 00:00:49,082
Descend, Dragonic Overlord!

18
00:00:49,082 --> 00:00:51,652
♪

19
00:00:51,652 --> 00:00:54,655
Impossible.

20
00:00:54,655 --> 00:00:57,591
(whimpering)

21
00:00:57,591 --> 00:01:00,093
(shouting)

22
00:01:00,093 --> 00:02:28,515
♪

23
00:02:32,085 --> 00:02:33,987
(indistinct chattering)

24
00:02:39,192 --> 00:02:41,595
(grunting)

25
00:02:41,595 --> 00:02:43,930
Hmm, we're finished here.

26
00:02:43,930 --> 00:02:47,300
I can't believe you beat
my Juggernaut Maximum.

27
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,835
What's with your luck, huh?

28
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:51,071
My luck?

29
00:02:51,071 --> 00:02:52,572
How dare he.

30
00:02:52,572 --> 00:02:54,608
Are you okay?

31
00:02:54,608 --> 00:02:56,810
Winning matches
as usual, eh, Kai?

32
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:57,878
Hmm?

33
00:02:57,878 --> 00:02:59,379
Miwa.

34
00:02:59,379 --> 00:03:02,349
Have you even lost a game
since you moved back here?

35
00:03:02,349 --> 00:03:03,917
No, not yet.

36
00:03:03,917 --> 00:03:05,519
Nice!

37
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:06,553
Hey there!

38
00:03:06,553 --> 00:03:08,055
Are any of your
regulars better

39
00:03:08,055 --> 00:03:10,624
at Vanguard than this guy?

40
00:03:10,624 --> 00:03:12,993
Don't know or care.

41
00:03:12,993 --> 00:03:14,061
That settles it.

42
00:03:14,061 --> 00:03:16,863
If she can't decide,
then I'll be the one.

43
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:19,032
Kai is the best!

44
00:03:19,032 --> 00:03:20,934
Hey, man, he's not that great!

45
00:03:20,934 --> 00:03:22,169
I almost had him.

46
00:03:22,169 --> 00:03:23,770
Nice try, loser.

47
00:03:23,770 --> 00:03:26,339
‐Hey!
‐Calm down!

48
00:03:26,339 --> 00:03:29,076
Is the sore loser sore
about being called "loser"?

49
00:03:29,076 --> 00:03:31,111
If he wasn't holding me
back, you'd be sorry!

50
00:03:31,111 --> 00:03:33,046
Yeah, right.

51
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:36,116
Is that all it
takes to be on top?

52
00:03:36,116 --> 00:03:39,186
These easy games are
a waste of my time.

53
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:44,458
Isn't there anyone
better around here?

54
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:55,402
♪

55
00:03:55,402 --> 00:03:57,337
With countless people
around the world

56
00:03:57,337 --> 00:03:59,206
playing trading card games,

57
00:03:59,206 --> 00:04:02,542
they've quickly become
a part of our daily lives.

58
00:04:04,444 --> 00:04:06,580
These days,
the biggest of them all

59
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:08,849
is Cardfight Vanguard.

60
00:04:08,849 --> 00:04:11,885
♪

61
00:04:11,885 --> 00:04:13,186
I never would have thought

62
00:04:13,186 --> 00:04:16,523
that a game could
change my life forever.

63
00:04:16,523 --> 00:04:18,825
♪

64
00:04:18,825 --> 00:04:20,460
And the battles
of Kawanakajima

65
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:22,295
reach their bloody climax!

66
00:04:22,295 --> 00:04:24,231
The fifth and final battle.

67
00:04:24,231 --> 00:04:27,501
The forces of Uesugi
numbering 12,000.

68
00:04:27,501 --> 00:04:30,504
Using a battle formation
known as "wheel winding"

