74
00:04:43,216 --> 00:04:46,787
Man, he's trying hard
to make this interesting.

75
00:04:46,787 --> 00:04:48,088
Yeah, no kidding,

76
00:04:48,088 --> 00:04:51,057
and he's not doing a very
good job of it, right, guys?

77
00:04:51,057 --> 00:04:54,361
Ahem, so, it's clear
this was a time period

78
00:04:54,361 --> 00:04:56,463
of life‐and‐death decisions.

79
00:04:56,463 --> 00:04:57,964
Let's see.

80
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:01,668
Answer me this, Aichi Sendou.

81
00:05:01,668 --> 00:05:03,537
Uh, yes?

82
00:05:03,537 --> 00:05:05,005
How would you
have stayed alive

83
00:05:05,005 --> 00:05:07,941
if you were transported to
the Warring States period?

84
00:05:07,941 --> 00:05:11,645
Well, I guess, I...

85
00:05:11,645 --> 00:05:13,380
Don't ask Shychi Aichi.

86
00:05:13,380 --> 00:05:15,215
He chose the
quietest kid in class.

87
00:05:15,215 --> 00:05:17,484
We're gonna be here
all afternoon.

88
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:19,553
Come on, Mr. Sendou.

89
00:05:19,553 --> 00:05:21,888
Imagine you're really there.

90
00:05:21,888 --> 00:05:24,191
I‐‐I guess...

91
00:05:24,191 --> 00:05:28,094
I guess I would make sure
I always had an escape plan.

92
00:05:30,130 --> 00:05:32,399
(laughing)

93
00:05:32,399 --> 00:05:34,134
He's such a coward.

94
00:05:34,134 --> 00:05:36,403
No wonder everybody
picks on him.

95
00:05:36,403 --> 00:05:38,738
There he
being weird again.

96
00:05:38,738 --> 00:05:40,340
What a great answer.

97
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,876
Man, oh, man,
you're hilarious.

98
00:05:42,876 --> 00:05:45,779
Well, you know,
it's not a bad plan

99
00:05:45,779 --> 00:05:48,281
if all you want
to do is stay alive.

100
00:05:48,281 --> 00:05:50,817
How about next time you
try imagining yourself

101
00:05:50,817 --> 00:05:52,752
with a bit bigger
role to play?

102
00:05:52,752 --> 00:05:55,589
I‐‐I'm sorry.

103
00:05:55,589 --> 00:05:58,925
Man, I sure messed that up.

104
00:05:58,925 --> 00:06:01,828
Now then, this battle
at Kawanakajima

105
00:06:01,828 --> 00:06:03,630
caused him to
lose his chance...

106
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:05,465
There's no way
that I would fit in

107
00:06:05,465 --> 00:06:07,834
with such amazing soldiers.

108
00:06:10,403 --> 00:06:11,671
Hmm.

109
00:06:11,671 --> 00:06:13,974
But I just know
he would be a hero

110
00:06:13,974 --> 00:06:15,775
in the Warring States period,

111
00:06:15,775 --> 00:06:18,545
the Vanguard warrior
Blaster Blade.

112
00:06:18,545 --> 00:06:22,282
♪

113
00:06:22,282 --> 00:06:24,217
Move it, scum!

114
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:26,353
I am Blaster Blade.

115
00:06:26,353 --> 00:06:29,522
I have come from
the United Sanctuary.

116
00:06:29,522 --> 00:06:31,858
Five, bring me his head.

117
00:06:31,858 --> 00:06:34,895
Let's go!

118
00:06:34,895 --> 00:06:37,063
Taste my pain.

119
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:38,832
Heh.

120
00:06:38,832 --> 00:06:41,635
Of course, he would never
have that chance again!

121
00:06:41,635 --> 00:06:44,337
This would haunt him
till the end of his days.

122
00:06:44,337 --> 00:06:45,772
Oh, man.

123
00:06:45,772 --> 00:06:47,107
I was hoping this pack
would have something

124
00:06:47,107 --> 00:06:49,609
strong enough
to beat that guy.

125
00:06:49,609 --> 00:06:51,478
I suck.

126
00:06:51,478 --> 00:06:54,047
No, it's all because of Kai.

127
00:06:54,047 --> 00:06:57,284
I used to be the best
player at that store.

128
00:06:57,284 --> 00:07:00,420
He thinks he can just waltz
in here with his cool hair

129
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:02,255
and beat me at my own game?

130
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:06,293
I've got to get my hands
on some better cards.

131
00:07:06,293 --> 00:07:10,230
Hey, what's that small
fry so happy about?

132
00:07:10,230 --> 00:07:14,234
Wait, that's a Vanguard card.

133
00:07:14,234 --> 00:07:16,670
And it's Blaster Blade!

134
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:20,340
That's the kind of rare
power card I'm looking for.

135
00:07:20,340 --> 00:07:23,310
♪

136
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:25,645
(clock chiming)

137
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:29,649
Wh‐‐what do you want from me?

138
00:07:31,151 --> 00:07:32,919
Hey there, Aichi.

139
00:07:32,919 --> 00:07:36,523
Why didn't you tell me you
were a Vanguard fighter?

140
00:07:36,523 --> 00:07:38,825
