141
00:07:38,825 --> 00:07:40,393
Don't play dumb.

142
00:07:40,393 --> 00:07:41,661
If you've got the cards,

143
00:07:41,661 --> 00:07:44,230
then you must be
familiar with the game.

144
00:07:44,230 --> 00:07:45,498
You've got some, right?

145
00:07:45,498 --> 00:07:48,134
Well, yeah, but I‐‐I‐‐

146
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:51,604
I never actually
use them or anything.

147
00:07:51,604 --> 00:07:54,207
I'm not what you think I am.

148
00:07:54,207 --> 00:07:55,608
‐Hmm.
‐Hmm.

149
00:07:55,608 --> 00:07:57,911
Yeah, whatever,
just show me the card

150
00:07:57,911 --> 00:07:59,412
you have hidden
in your pocket.

151
00:07:59,412 --> 00:08:01,414
(whimpering)

152
00:08:01,414 --> 00:08:04,818
♪

153
00:08:04,818 --> 00:08:07,921
Ha‐ha, no way,
it is Blaster Blade!

154
00:08:07,921 --> 00:08:11,224
With this, I could
finally beat that show‐off.

155
00:08:11,224 --> 00:08:13,093
Oh, let me see!

156
00:08:13,093 --> 00:08:14,728
Whoa, cool!

157
00:08:14,728 --> 00:08:16,496
How about we go
to Card Capital?

158
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:17,564
‐Yeah!
‐Wait.

159
00:08:17,564 --> 00:08:18,999
Morikawa.

160
00:08:18,999 --> 00:08:20,166
That's mine!

161
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:21,568
It was a special gift!

162
00:08:21,568 --> 00:08:23,503
You can't take it
away from me!

163
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:26,639
‐Wait!
‐Oops.

164
00:08:26,639 --> 00:08:27,774
Don't push it.

165
00:08:27,774 --> 00:08:30,810
You're not a Vanguard
fighter anyway.

166
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:34,280
A card this awesome
deserves to battle every day,

167
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,950
so I'll take it off
your hands, buddy.

168
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:38,885
Okay, let's get
to Card Capital!

169
00:08:38,885 --> 00:08:40,186
Yeah!

170
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:42,622
Gi‐‐give it back.

171
00:08:42,622 --> 00:08:44,657
That's not yours, you can't‐‐

172
00:08:44,657 --> 00:08:47,193
♪

173
00:08:48,695 --> 00:08:50,797
(indistinct chattering)

174
00:08:52,365 --> 00:08:54,501
(panting)

175
00:08:54,501 --> 00:08:55,635
Huh?

176
00:08:55,635 --> 00:08:57,103
I challenge.

177
00:08:57,103 --> 00:08:59,172
Huh, you're no challenge.

178
00:08:59,172 --> 00:09:02,108
You talk like a big shot,
but I want a rematch

179
00:09:02,108 --> 00:09:05,745
to decide who's best in
the shop once and for all.

180
00:09:05,745 --> 00:09:06,913
No thanks.

181
00:09:06,913 --> 00:09:08,048
What?

182
00:09:08,048 --> 00:09:10,150
You're not very
good at this game.

183
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:13,386
You lack foresight and your
strategy is pretty weak.

184
00:09:13,386 --> 00:09:16,022
All you care about
is brute force.

185
00:09:16,022 --> 00:09:18,958
Playing you again would
just be a waste of my time,

186
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:20,527
so why bother?

187
00:09:20,527 --> 00:09:23,063
Dude, that's harsh.

188
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:25,365
You won't get anything
out of it, huh?

189
00:09:25,365 --> 00:09:28,468
Well, then, if you beat me,
you can have this card.

190
00:09:28,468 --> 00:09:30,904
Oh, wow, that's Blaster Blade!

191
00:09:30,904 --> 00:09:33,940
Those things are super
rare, man, that's great!

192
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:35,375
Blaster Blade?

193
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:37,644
Could it be that card?

194
00:09:37,644 --> 00:09:38,912
Shall we?

195
00:09:38,912 --> 00:09:40,814
Fine.

196
00:09:40,814 --> 00:09:42,849
Oh, it's on then.

197
00:09:42,849 --> 00:09:45,919
♪

198
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:48,521
My‐‐my card.

199
00:09:50,390 --> 00:09:52,258
Oh, man, come on!

200
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:54,427
Why is my luck so bad today?

201
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:57,197
Your luck doesn't matter.

202
00:09:57,197 --> 00:10:00,333
Now ride the Vanguard!

203
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:02,502
♪

204
00:10:02,502 --> 00:10:06,206
I'm pretty sure that this
is the place he mentioned.

205
00:10:06,206 --> 00:10:08,775
♪

206
00:10:08,775 --> 00:10:11,311
That's six damaged, so I win.

207
00:10:11,311 --> 00:10:12,445
Oh!

208
00:10:12,445 --> 00:10:13,580
No way!

209
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:15,715
Let's play again.

210
00:10:15,715 --> 00:10:17,383
We're finished here.

211
00:10:17,383 --> 00:10:20,787
Hey, heads‐up, buddy.

212
00:10:20,787 --> 00:10:22,856
Blaster Blade.

213
00:10:22,856 --> 00:10:25,592
Hey, man, cheer up, you won.

214
00:10:25,592 --> 00:10:28,094
Gi‐‐give me my card back.

215
00:10:28,094 --> 00:10:30,196
‐Who's this?
‐Aichi.

216
00:10:30,196 --> 00:10:32,699
Morikawa, hand it over.

217
00:10:32,699 --> 00:10:34,601
Come on, it means
a lot to me!

218
00:10:34,601 --> 00:10:36,703
Hey, I don't have it.

219
00:10:36,703 --> 00:10:38,004
A missing card.

220
00:10:38,004 --> 00:10:40,306
Do you mean that one?

221
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:41,641
Yeah, that's it.

222
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:44,777
That's my card.

223
00:10:44,777 --> 00:10:46,913
Please, give it back.

224
00:10:46,913 --> 00:10:48,248
No way.

225
00:10:48,248 --> 00:10:50,583
This card belongs to me.

226
00:10:50,583 --> 00:10:56,322
♪

227
00:10:59,692 --> 00:11:03,730
♪

228
00:11:05,732 --> 00:11:07,267
Hey.

229
00:11:07,267 --> 00:11:08,935
Huh?

230
00:11:08,935 --> 00:11:10,370
Uh...

231
00:11:13,072 --> 00:11:15,808
It's important that we respect
the terms and conditions

232
00:11:15,808 --> 00:11:18,044
of a Vanguard battle,
don't you think?

233
00:11:18,044 --> 00:11:22,182
This guy bet me
the card and lost.

234
00:11:22,182 --> 00:11:24,017
(grunting)

235
00:11:24,017 --> 00:11:26,653
‐Well, can I have it?
‐Sorry, kid.

236
00:11:26,653 --> 00:11:28,254
When you lose a
card in battle,

237
00:11:28,254 --> 00:11:31,991
you've got to fight
to get it back.

238
00:11:31,991 --> 00:11:34,894
Well then, why don't
you fight me for it?

239
00:11:34,894 --> 00:11:36,029
Huh?

240
00:11:36,029 --> 00:11:37,997
(gasping)

241
00:11:39,799 --> 00:11:42,835
Hmm, okay, kid, it's a deal.

242
00:11:42,835 --> 00:11:45,405
Hold on, you can't fight him!

243
00:11:45,405 --> 00:11:47,840
You've never even
played Vanguard before.

244
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:49,943
You don't have
a deck, do you?

245
00:11:49,943 --> 00:11:53,379
It's true, I've never played.

246
00:11:53,379 --> 00:11:54,814
But I built this deck

247
00:11:54,814 --> 00:11:57,550
just in case I ever
got the chance to play.

248
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:59,352
Say what?

249
00:11:59,352 --> 00:12:02,455
Take a seat and get comfy.

250
00:12:02,455 --> 00:12:06,292
Move it along, loser boy.

251
00:12:06,292 --> 00:12:07,760
(meowing)

252
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:09,996
What are you so
happy about, huh?

253
00:12:09,996 --> 00:12:11,130
This battle.

254
00:12:11,130 --> 00:12:12,565
We're about to
witness a match

255
00:12:12,565 --> 00:12:14,500
between the best
player in the store

256
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,169
and a guy who's
never played the game.

257
00:12:16,169 --> 00:12:17,837
This is gonna be hilarious!

258
00:12:17,837 --> 00:12:19,606
Stop saying Kai's the best.

259
00:12:19,606 --> 00:12:22,075
With the right cards,
I'm sure I could have...

260
00:12:22,075 --> 00:12:26,312
♪

261
00:12:26,312 --> 00:12:27,814
Since this is
your first time,

262
00:12:27,814 --> 00:12:29,983
I'll explain the
rules as we go, okay?

263
00:12:29,983 --> 00:12:32,185
‐Sure.
‐Oh, yeah.

264
00:12:32,185 --> 00:12:34,287
You're not gonna stand
much of a chance against me

265
00:12:34,287 --> 00:12:37,290
unless you have this Blaster
Blade back in your deck.

266
00:12:37,290 --> 00:12:38,992
Yes, that's right.

267
00:12:38,992 --> 00:12:43,263
So, you can borrow it until
I beat you and take it back.

268
00:12:43,263 --> 00:12:44,998
Blaster Blade.

269
00:12:44,998 --> 00:12:48,067
Th‐‐thank you.

270
00:12:48,067 --> 00:12:49,402
You're lending him a card

