00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:54,807
How unusually
sweet of you, Kai.

273
00:12:54,807 --> 00:12:56,142
Are you finished?

274
00:12:56,142 --> 00:12:58,311
I'm only gonna explain
the rules once,

275
00:12:58,311 --> 00:13:00,046
so you better listen.

276
00:13:00,046 --> 00:13:02,248
‐Let's start.
‐Right.

277
00:13:02,248 --> 00:13:04,017
Now, imagine it.

278
00:13:04,017 --> 00:13:06,586
Our spirits have just been
transported to the surface

279
00:13:06,586 --> 00:13:09,856
of a planet similar
to Earth called "Cray".

280
00:13:11,557 --> 00:13:15,194
In this form, there are only
two powers available to us,

281
00:13:15,194 --> 00:13:16,929
the first of which

282
00:13:16,929 --> 00:13:20,033
allows us to summon the
monsters of this planet.

283
00:13:20,033 --> 00:13:22,302
The cards in your
deck are your units.

284
00:13:22,302 --> 00:13:23,469
Call to them.

285
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:26,506
But, first, we both need
to draw our starting hands.

286
00:13:26,506 --> 00:13:28,408
Got all that?

287
00:13:28,408 --> 00:13:32,378
The cards you draw can both
attack and defend for you.

288
00:13:33,713 --> 00:13:36,249
These are your units.

289
00:13:36,249 --> 00:13:38,084
Hmm.

290
00:13:38,084 --> 00:13:40,553
Each card has its
own grade and powers.

291
00:13:40,553 --> 00:13:43,556
Any other abilities
will be on the card.

292
00:13:43,556 --> 00:13:45,825
♪

293
00:13:45,825 --> 00:13:48,428
And, then, there is
the second power

294
00:13:48,428 --> 00:13:50,363
of our spirit form.

295
00:13:50,363 --> 00:13:54,167
The power to ride is to
possess one of our units.

296
00:13:54,167 --> 00:13:55,968
‐Oh, really?
‐Oh, dude.

297
00:13:55,968 --> 00:13:58,905
The units that we merge with
are called our "Vanguards."

298
00:13:58,905 --> 00:14:00,273
You follow?

299
00:14:00,273 --> 00:14:04,377
The word "vanguard" means
"the one that leads the way."

300
00:14:04,377 --> 00:14:07,680
The Vanguard leads the way.

301
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:11,050
Now, the object of the game
is to defeat your opponent

302
00:14:11,050 --> 00:14:14,387
by landing attacks
on their Vanguard.

303
00:14:14,387 --> 00:14:17,290
The card in front of you is
a grade zero unit, right?

304
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:20,560
‐Yes.
‐Okay, flip it over.

305
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:23,763
Ready, stand up the Vanguard.

306
00:14:23,763 --> 00:14:26,132
Lizard Runner, Undeux.

307
00:14:26,132 --> 00:14:28,101
For me?

308
00:14:28,101 --> 00:14:31,003
Stardust Trumpeter, stand up.

309
00:14:31,003 --> 00:14:35,608
♪

310
00:14:35,608 --> 00:14:39,312
Our Vanguards are ready for
battle on the planet Cray.

311
00:14:39,312 --> 00:14:40,913
It'll be easier
for me to explain

312
00:14:40,913 --> 00:14:43,049
if I take the
first turn, okay?

313
00:14:43,049 --> 00:14:44,550
Sure.

314
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:47,353
You start each turn
by drawing a card.

315
00:14:47,353 --> 00:14:49,389
Each turn, you can
promote your Vanguard

316
00:14:49,389 --> 00:14:52,959
using a unit of no more
than one grade above.

317
00:14:52,959 --> 00:14:56,329
Stack that unit on
top of the Vanguard.

318
00:14:56,329 --> 00:14:59,499
Ride the Embodiment
of Armor, Bahr.

319
00:14:59,499 --> 00:15:01,667
Now, once your
Vanguard is promoted,

320
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:03,936
you can summon lower
grade support units

321
00:15:03,936 --> 00:15:05,438
to the battlefield.

322
00:15:05,438 --> 00:15:07,940
These are called
the "rear guard".

323
00:15:07,940 --> 00:15:10,943
I call the Flame
of Hope, Aermo.

324
00:15:10,943 --> 00:15:17,450
♪

325
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:19,886
I now have two
units on the field,

326
00:15:19,886 --> 00:15:21,788
and with them, I attack.

327
00:15:21,788 --> 00:15:23,256
Huh?

328
00:15:23,256 --> 00:15:26,025
Except that you can't
attack on your first turn.

329
00:15:26,025 --> 00:15:27,760
(sighing)

330
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,796
The downside of going first.

331
00:15:29,796 --> 00:15:31,664
It's your turn.

332
00:15:31,664 --> 00:15:34,634
Right, I'll draw a card.

333
00:15:34,634 --> 00:15:36,302
Then, I'll promote.

334
00:15:36,302 --> 00:15:39,806
Ride Little Sage, Marron!

335
00:15:39,806 --> 00:15:43,409
And call Wingal, too!

336
00:15:43,409 --> 00:15:47,280
♪

337
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:50,750
Well, it looks like we both
have two units in play.

338
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:52,318
So are you attacking?

339
00:15:52,318 --> 00:15:54,387
I‐‐I'll attack you.

340
00:15:54,387 --> 00:15:55,855
Okay, then do it.

341
00:15:55,855 --> 00:15:58,958
Turn your Vanguard
to signal the attack.

342
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:01,394
Then I attack your Bahr
with Little Sage, Marron.

343
00:16:01,394 --> 00:16:04,230
When your Vanguard attacks,
you can increase its power

344
00:16:04,230 --> 00:16:07,633
by supporting it with
one of your rear‐guard.

345
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:09,635
In that case, I'll
add Wingal's power

346
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:13,272
to Marron's attack.

347
00:16:13,272 --> 00:16:14,774
When your Vanguard attacks,

348
00:16:14,774 --> 00:16:16,876
you need to reveal the
top card of your deck

349
00:16:16,876 --> 00:16:19,979
and check for
a drive trigger.

350
00:16:21,514 --> 00:16:24,317
Look for a mark in
the upper‐right corner.

351
00:16:24,317 --> 00:16:26,686
If there isn't one,
add it to your hand.

352
00:16:26,686 --> 00:16:29,522
Then, my attack went through?

353
00:16:29,522 --> 00:16:32,358
Uh‐huh.

354
00:16:32,358 --> 00:16:33,392
Okay.

355
00:16:33,392 --> 00:16:36,496
Your attack
overwhelmed my Vanguard.

356
00:16:36,496 --> 00:16:39,799
This is the damage
from that hit.

357
00:16:39,799 --> 00:16:42,702
Now, if you can deal me
five more damage,

358
00:16:42,702 --> 00:16:44,537
then my forces will banish

359
00:16:44,537 --> 00:16:46,272
from the surface
of the planet.

360
00:16:46,272 --> 00:16:48,241
That means I lose.

361
00:16:48,241 --> 00:16:49,642
Does it all make sense?

362
00:16:49,642 --> 00:16:50,710
Uh, yeah.

363
00:16:50,710 --> 00:16:52,645
Well, it's good to see
that you're catching on.

364
00:16:52,645 --> 00:16:53,946
It's my turn.

365
00:16:53,946 --> 00:16:57,550
Rid the Dragon
Knight, Nehalem.

366
00:16:57,550 --> 00:17:00,820
I call Bahr.

367
00:17:00,820 --> 00:17:02,989
♪

368
00:17:02,989 --> 00:17:05,758
Ride the Vanguard.

369
00:17:05,758 --> 00:17:08,628
No more Mr. Nice Kai, eh?

370
00:17:08,628 --> 00:17:10,997
Aichi doesn't stand a chance.

371
00:17:10,997 --> 00:17:12,899
(laughing)

372
00:17:14,567 --> 00:17:17,270
I attack Marron with Bahr.

373
00:17:17,270 --> 00:17:19,372
Um, Bahr and Marron both have

374
00:17:19,372 --> 00:17:21,941
the exact same attack
power, so then...

375
00:17:21,941 --> 00:17:24,644
If the power is equal,
the attack goes through.

376
00:17:24,644 --> 00:17:26,712
But if this attack
goes through now,

377
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:27,914
you'll be able
to hit me again

378
00:17:27,914 --> 00:17:30,550
with the Dragon Knight,
Nehalem afterwards,

379
00:17:30,550 --> 00:17:32,652
and I'll take
two damage, right?

380
00:17:32,652 --> 00:17:34,921
Yes, but you can weaken
your opponent's attack

381
00:17:34,921 --> 00:17:38,324
by defending with the
cards in your hand.

382
00:17:38,324 --> 00:17:42,061
Then, I guard with the
Bringer of Good Luck, Epona.

383
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:43,796
The number on the
side of the card

384
00:17:43,796 --> 00:17:46,198
becomes your damage shield.

385
00:17:46,198 --> 00:17:49,535
Bahr's power isn't high
enough to break through.

386
00:17:49,535 --> 00:17:51,704
My attack has no effect.

387
00:17:51,704 --> 00:17:53,573
But now that card
you defended with

388
00:17:53,573 --> 00:17:57,043
has to go into the drop zone.

389
00:17:57,043 --> 00:18:00,346
Next, I attack Marron with
the Dragon Knight, Nehalem,

390
00:18:00,346 --> 00:18:03,316
combined with the
rear guard's power.

391
00:18:03,316 --> 00:18:05,384
I don't guard.

392
00:18:05,384 --> 00:18:09,655
Not that I need it, but I'll
check for a drive trigger.

393
00:18:09,655 --> 00:18:11,657
(shouting)

394
00:18:11,657 --> 00:18:15,127
♪

395
00:18:15,127 --> 00:18:17,430
'Kay, now it's your move.

396
00:18:17,430 --> 00:18:19,765
Right.

397
00:18:19,765 --> 00:18:21,534
We both have one damage each.

398
00:18:21,534 --> 00:18:23,436
All right.

399
00:18:23,436 --> 00:18:26,806
Ride the Knight of
Silence, Gallatin!

400
00:18:26,806 --> 00:18:30,142
♪

401
00:18:30,142 --> 00:18:33,512
And, also, I call
Marron and Flogal.

402
00:18:33,512 --> 00:18:35,881
I use Gallatin with
the support of Wingal

403
00:18:35,881 --> 00:18:38,050
to attack Nehalem!

404
00:18:38,050 --> 00:18:40,987
♪

405
00:18:40,987 --> 00:18:42,922
Then Marron with
the power of Flogal

406
00:18:42,922 --> 00:18:46,092
will attack Nehalem again!

407
00:18:46,092 --> 00:18:49,261
I can't let you do that.

408
00:18:49,261 --> 00:18:51,597
Your attempt fails.

409
00:18:51,597 --> 00:18:55,801
Then, in that case,
I guess my turn's over.

410
00:18:55,801 --> 00:18:59,005
But I did cause one damage.

411
00:18:59,005 --> 00:19:01,440
If we continue trading
damage like this,

412
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:03,576
I'll just barely win.

413
00:19:03,576 --> 00:19:06,479
Hmm, why do you
look so relieved?

414
00:19:06,479 --> 00:19:10,750
Did you seriously think I was
gonna let it end this way?

415
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:13,686
Time for your final lesson.

416
00:19:13,686 --> 00:19:17,890
I call Wyvern Strike,
Tejas and Jarran.

417
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:19,825
(grunting)

418
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:21,427
Picture it.

419
00:19:21,427 --> 00:19:23,863
The assault that
I'm about to begin.

420
00:19:23,863 --> 00:19:25,798
(gulping)

421
00:19:25,798 --> 00:19:29,035
First, I attack
Marron with Bahr.

422
00:19:29,035 --> 00:19:31,037
I guard with Flogal.

423
00:19:32,371 --> 00:19:34,573
Ha, then I come for Gallatin

424
00:19:34,573 --> 00:19:38,077
with the combined might
of Jarron and Tejas.

425
00:19:39,412 --> 00:19:41,013
I can't stop that.

426
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:43,382
That's right, and these
two get a special bonus

427
00:19:43,382 --> 00:19:44,583
for supporting each other.

428
00:19:44,583 --> 00:19:47,486
An extra 4,000 power.

429
00:19:47,486 --> 00:19:50,690
♪

430
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:52,692
(firing)

431
00:19:52,692 --> 00:19:54,960
♪

432
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,929
Now I have two
damage, as well.

433
00:19:56,929 --> 00:19:57,963
Guess we're tied.

434
00:19:57,963 --> 00:20:01,233
Oh, who said I was
finished attacking you?

435
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:04,937
I attack Gallatin with
Nehalem, supported by Aermo.

436
00:20:04,937 --> 00:20:07,039
Over 16,000?

437
00:20:07,039 --> 00:20:10,342
Are you sure that's all?

438
00:20:10,342 --> 00:20:11,577
Hmm.

439
00:20:11,577 --> 00:20:13,345
Embodiment of Spear, Tahr,

440
00:20:13,345 --> 00:20:16,816
but just look
what's in the corner.

441
00:20:16,816 --> 00:20:19,218
When this mark appears
on a card, you draw.

442
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:22,121
It gives you a 5,000
attack power bonus,

443
00:20:22,121 --> 00:20:24,423
and it also increases
the damage of the attack

444
00:20:24,423 --> 00:20:25,958
by one point.

445
00:20:25,958 --> 00:20:28,160
Then‐‐then that means...

446
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:30,262
This one is gonna hit
you for two damage,

447
00:20:30,262 --> 00:20:33,432
and once I get the lead,
I don't give it up.

448
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:37,436
(gasping)

449
00:20:37,436 --> 00:20:39,438
(zapping)

450
00:20:39,438 --> 00:20:41,607
♪

451
00:20:41,607 --> 00:20:43,509
(grunting)

452
00:20:46,045 --> 00:20:48,447
(shouting)

453
00:20:49,949 --> 00:20:51,884
(gasping)

454
00:20:51,884 --> 00:20:53,686
Are you okay, man?

455
00:20:53,686 --> 00:20:56,789
Uh‐huh.

456
00:20:56,789 --> 00:20:58,257
Two damage.

457
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:00,359
Putting me at
a total of four.

458
00:21:00,359 --> 00:21:02,461
This is bad.

459
00:21:02,461 --> 00:21:04,497
You were able to
picture it, I see.

460
00:21:04,497 --> 00:21:07,366
Witness true Vanguard.

461
00:21:10,603 --> 00:21:13,072
Guess it's all over.

462
00:21:13,072 --> 00:21:15,775
If it was me, I could
still make a comeback.

463
00:21:15,775 --> 00:21:18,711
For sure.

464
00:21:18,711 --> 00:21:20,679
It's your turn.

465
00:21:25,184 --> 00:21:28,320
Uh, mm.

466
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:29,588
What's up?

467
00:21:29,588 --> 00:21:33,159
Have you lost the will
to continue fighting?

468
00:21:33,159 --> 00:21:35,494
(laughing)

469
00:21:35,494 --> 00:21:37,496
Aichi?

470
00:21:37,496 --> 00:21:38,998
You're really good,

471
00:21:38,998 --> 00:21:43,135
but, still, this battle
is a lot of fun.

472
00:21:43,135 --> 00:21:46,806
♪

473
00:21:46,806 --> 00:21:49,041
Do you know him or something?

474
00:21:49,041 --> 00:21:50,843
I always hoped that one day

475
00:21:50,843 --> 00:21:53,813
I would get the chance
to battle with you.

476
00:21:53,813 --> 00:21:57,883
So then you're
Aichi Sendou, right?

477
00:21:59,051 --> 00:22:00,753
That's right, Kai.

478
00:22:00,753 --> 00:22:05,457
And you gave me the power to
stand here before you today.

479
00:22:05,457 --> 00:22:07,026
I see.

480
00:22:07,026 --> 00:22:08,561
Let's go.

481
00:22:08,561 --> 00:22:11,730
Arise my avatar, ride!

482
00:22:13,432 --> 00:22:16,769
(grunting)

483
00:22:16,769 --> 00:22:19,972
Blaster Blade!

484
00:22:19,972 --> 00:22:23,042
♪

485
00:22:26,679 --> 00:23:55,935
♪

486
00:23:59,972 --> 00:24:01,707
You're really good,
but, still,

487
00:24:01,707 --> 00:24:03,876
this battle is
a lot of fun, Kai.

488
00:24:03,876 --> 00:24:05,878
Sendou, right?

489
00:24:05,878 --> 00:24:07,713
You guys know each other?

490
00:24:07,713 --> 00:24:10,849
Yes, the one who gave
me this Blaster Blade,

491
00:24:10,849 --> 00:24:12,184
and the one who made me think

492
00:24:12,184 --> 00:24:14,286
of becoming a
Vanguard fighter.

493
00:24:14,286 --> 00:24:16,322
The person who
started it all?

494
00:24:16,322 --> 00:24:18,223
Are we finished talking now?

495
00:24:18,223 --> 00:24:20,793
On the next
<i>Cardfight!! Vanguard,</i>

496
00:24:20,793 --> 00:24:22,328
"Ride to Victory!"

497
00:24:22,328 --> 00:24:25,230
Now, whenever
you're ready, Aichi,

498
00:24:25,230 --> 00:24:28,267
picture our Vanguard
fight in your mind.

